{
  "doc_id": "43614",
  "text": "The power achieved for the frequency division-by-three SRO is at least ten times higher than previously reported in the literature [CITATION_1] . This is the first time a cw harmonic comb of up to six harmonics has been reported. The total harmonic comb power of 7.4 W is unprecedented. High cw power is needed for effective phase and amplitude management of the comb components in waveform synthesis [CITATION_2] and its subsequent applications. The multiwatt comb power that has been achieved is expected to be sufficient for this purpose.",
